   Synthesize the results to determine if the graviton condensate framework provides a self-consistent alternative to inflaton-based models. Compare the derived $n_s$ and $r$ scaling relations against standard inflationary benchmarks to conclude whether the memory burden mechanism is a viable candidate for explaining the early universe's expansion and the origin of primordial fluctuations.
