   Derive the power spectrum of curvature perturbations $\mathcal{P}_\zeta$ and tensor perturbations $\mathcal{P}_t$ by treating the Bogoliubov modes as quantum fluctuations on the condensate background. Use the fluctuation-dissipation theorem to relate the variance of the memory modes $\langle b_k^\dagger b_k \rangle$ to the energy density fluctuations of the condensate. Express the spectral index $n_s - 1 \approx d \ln \mathcal{P}_\zeta / d \ln k$ and the tensor-to-scalar ratio $r = \mathcal{P}_t / \mathcal{P}_\zeta$ as functions of the feedback parameters $\gamma$ and $N_s$.

