   Derive the functional form of the memory load $Q_{mem} \sim N_s F(M_{Pl}/H)$ from the entropy-area relation and the holographic principle. Compare power-law, logarithmic, and constant forms of $F$ to determine which is theoretically consistent with the species bound $N_s \leq S_{dS}$. Use this derivation to replace the previous parameterization with a physically motivated expression based on the information-theoretic capacity of the horizon.

